description:
While John Knox was initially reluctant to become a preacher, once he accepted the call he moved forward with sheer determination and courage. This episode delves deeper into his Reformation journey. At this time, Mary Queen of Scots was ruling, and she had a fearsome reputation, causing many a strong man to wilt in her presence. But this was not true of John Knox. An encounter that took place in Holyrood Palace stands to us as an example, inspiring courage in the face of danger and peril.

To find out more about John Knox visit our website to read our extended article.
